</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Peak Months for Coho Runs</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    The best time to target Coho near Eugene is from <strong>mid-September through early November</strong>. During these months, water temperatures and flow rates are optimal for salmon migration.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Early Morning vs Late Evening Bites</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Coho are more active during low-light conditions. Early morning and late evening are prime times to fish, especially on sunny days when the water is clear.
</p>
<h2>
    <strong>Licenses and Regulations</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Before heading out, it’s essential to stay compliant with Oregon fishing laws.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Oregon Fishing License Requirements</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Anglers aged 12 and older need a valid <strong>Oregon angling license</strong>, and a <strong>Combined Angling Tag</strong> if targeting salmon. These are available at local bait shops and online via the <strong>ODFW website</strong>.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Daily Bag Limits &amp; Legal Methods</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Typically, you can keep <strong>two adult Coho per day</strong>, but limits vary by location and year. Always check current regulations on the <strong>ODFW Fishing Report</strong> before fishing.
</p>
